Caterpillar 94 / 110 A (
Figure 4
), which appeared to be in the final instar, measured 17mm . Head oval, widest near base; matt translucent dull green; stemmata black. Body dull yellow-green; dorsal line dark green, bordered by subdorsal whitish line; dorsolateral line pale yellow, with a dark green border dorsally and laterally; spiracles pale, inconspicuous; all legs concolorous.
